The federal government has said that there are no plans to dismantle the electricity distribution companies (DisCos). The minister of State for Power, Goddy Jedy Agba stated this Thursday in Abuja while fielding questions from newsmen during his working visit to the Corporate Headquarters of Abuja Electricity Distribution Company (AEDC). The minister who commended AEDC’s effort and preparedness towards metering and improving electricity supply to its customers noted, “I don’t think anybody is thinking of dismantling the DisCos, rather, the focus is to revamp and make them perform optimally.” Recall that at a time there were rumours making the round that the federal government was contemplating revoking the licences of the operators over poor performance. He said what AEDC has put in place shows that the company is doing well. “I have gone round their facilities, and from what I have seen, AEDC is a one-stop centre for Power distribution in Nigeria. I am very glad over what the CEO and his team have put in place. Location of faults or problems in real time is a solution to the distribution problem. “My major concern here is metering, but I can see they are making a lot of effort at Abuja DisCo and they have metered many of their customers. But there is still room for improvement,’ he said. Speaking, the minister’s host and MD/CEO of AEDC, Engr Ernest Mupuwaya, said his company is working tirelessly to ensure that all its customers are metered in good time, except for some challenges that are slowing down the pace.